Raising a question that came up from my team while using the SDK.

One of my team members was confused by the [Parent-Child streams](https://gitlab.com/meltano/sdk/-/blob/main/docs/parent_streams.md) docs. Specifically, they weren't sure how `group_id` was used in the path of `EpicIssuesStream`, they new it was in the context, but thought it was being set as an instance property and were confused why it wasn't working.

I explained that there was probably a method like this that was implied to exist, and that the SDK does parameter replacement in paths:

```python
    def get_url_params(
        self, context: Optional[dict], next_page_token: Optional[Any]
    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
       return { 'group_id': context['group_id'], 'epic_iid': context['epic_iid'], 'page': next_page_token }
```

Might be something to consider adding/refining.
